    <item>
      <title>Progress demands a progressive media landscape</title>
      <link>https://www.dhakatribune.com/opinion/editorial/409821/progress-demands-a-progressive-media-landscape</link>
      <description>National and international speakers at a recent discussion rightfully underscored that democracy and tolerance are inseparable from a free media.

To that end, it is truly unfortunate how our nation’s media landscape continues to struggle under pressures that undermine both freedom and responsibility.

Bangladesh speaks of progress and democratic ideals, yet without creating the appropriate conditions where journalism can flourish without fear, censorship, or arbitrary control, such a goal will continue to be out of reach.

Indeed, we must acknowledge that our media landscape remains caught between political suspicion and economic vulnerability. Every government has looked at criticism as hostility, using laws and regulations to silence dissent rather than encourage debate. Simultaneously, media outlets themselves continue to face financial fragility and thus susceptible to influence and compromise.

The result has thus been as expected: A press that too often operates under constraint and unable to fully serve its intended role.

It is time to do better. Governments must accept that criticism is not disloyalty but accountability while citizens too must recognize that a free press is not a threat but a safeguard.

Journalists and media personnel too have their own roles to play by upholding the highest standards of accuracy, fairness, and responsibility.

The progress of Bangladesh must be reflected in a more progressive media landscape. Our democratic ideals cannot mature without such a press - indeed, it is a foundational element to democratic governance.

If the government is serious about building a nation that espouses fundamental rights, freedom of speech, and accountability within the governance system, it must begin by ensuring that the media can operate freely, responsibly, and without fear.</description>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.dhakatribune.com/opinion/editorial/409821/progress-demands-a-progressive-media-landscape</guid>
